  "device_name": "GoPro",
  "device_description": "Gilpin et al. 2017 used weatherproof action cams (GoPro Hero 3) to monitor pollinator visitation to the inflorescences of two species (Lavandula angustifolia and Canna sp.) and compared the recorded video footage to manual observations. These cameras performed identically to direct manual observations except for the number of flowers in the field of view, which was underestimated. Action cams were found to offer high resolution recordings and hardware robustness, but were limited in their depth of field, power supply and subsequent recording duration (1–2 h).",
